															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pig-catapult" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(233556); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=233556&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183044" alt="Pig_catapult" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=233556)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pig-catapult" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(233556); return false;" >Pig_catapult</a></span> <span class="odate time_1404881709 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Jul 2014 04:55</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2066000">
									

<p>Because I wanted to get the story I couldn't tell with the SCP-023 article itself out in the 'verse instead of relegating hints of it to the discussion page and The Leak.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[Minor&nbsp;spoilers]</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>While worded poetically, &quot;the passions of the dead&quot; is still a literal description.<br />
&quot;My-children-who-birthed-me&quot; is half metaphorical and half literal.<br />
&quot;The light that brings life&quot; is literally just the sun.<br />
The title is a hint about the narrator, and the apostrophe placement was very deliberate.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[Major&nbsp;spoilers]</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The narrator and SCP-023 are both abstract entities born from the emotions of dying humans. The more people die feeling a given emotion, the more &quot;vast&quot; the corresponding abstract entity. The narrator embodies protective maternal love, and cannot help but regard humanity as her children even though she's aware the relationship is factually reversed. SCP-023, on the other hand, was born during the Black Death, and when people are dying of plague faster than you can dig graves, sometimes you just gotta throw the corpses into a big pit and set it on fire.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

