															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/milotic6312" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3475308); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3475308&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183044" alt="Milotic6312" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3475308)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/milotic6312" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3475308); return false;" >Milotic6312</a></span> <span class="odate time_1515605232 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Jan 2018 17:27</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3678302">
									

<p>I really enjoy myself some metaphors and symbolism, but I felt myself doubting whether things were metaphorical, what the metaphor was, or if they were just other Skippy-type things. Thanks to Pig_catapult that was all cleared up, but I still have a couple doubts. I caught that “my-children-who-birthed-me” was humanity, but I didn’t know what part of it or who “me” is. The Black Plague was picked up by me too, and it was probably the clearest metaphor, at least to someone who knows anything about medieval Europe. I suspected the narrator to be 023, but the end disproved that, leaving me wondering about the narrator (which I would LOVE to read more about, by the way). I think there should be more reason why this was attached to 023’s profile, maybe just something that said it was a note from somewhere?<br />
You’ve really got this going in an interesting direction and I’d want it to keep going, but there are some p(l)otholes in the road. I like the mystery element, but either there’s still something critical left out or if I just don’t understand.<br />
TL;DR I want more story because I look forward to its progression but also because I am confusion?¿?</p>

							</div>

								
					
